sentences: Émile Parisien (born 12 October 1982), is a French soprano and alto saxophonist, jazz musician, and composer.
From 1996, he studied at the Conservatoire de Toulouse, where he also studied classical and contemporary music.

During these years, he has had the opportunity to perform alongside major jazz figures such as Wynton Marsalis, Christian McBride, Johnny Griffin and Bobby Hutcherson, during the Jazz in Marciac festival.
Parisien moved to Paris in 2000 and in 2004 founded his own quartet with Julien Touery (piano), Ivan Gélugne (double bass), and Sylvain Darrifourcq (drums).
